Things are getting more interesting by the day on Uzalo. Mastermind, played by Ntokozo Dlamini, has returned to the streets of KwaMashu to reclaim his spot as the town’s bad boy. Although he is starting off on a clean slate righting his wrongs, the mischievous side of him couldn’t stay away. Within a day of his return he is already causing havoc and keeping people on their toes. Many people had been complaining that the show is no longer the same as the storyline has taken a dramatic turn since the exit of members of the original cast. They have been calling for their return. It’s good to see that producers and writers of the show have listened. ALSO READ | MPUMI MZOBE INVOLVED IN A CAR ACCIDENT There is a serious witch hunt on Durban Gen. This comes as Gog’Radebe’s weird behaviour in how she handles certain things has added more fuel to the fire and makes Mrs Dlamini even more suspicious that she is a witch. Accusing someone of being a witch can create a serious threat to their life if people react badly and cause them harm. How will it all pan out? A huge can of worms has been opened on Skeem Saam, as Lehasa’s arrest causes more unrest than peace as new evidence emerges. In the past, Lehasa has dodged going to jail many times. Will his sins catch up with him this time?